{
  "stem": "20083.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But since I was still 16 years old at the time, and you could be a, a member of the Kindertransport until the age of 16, she said she would try everything to get me out as quickly as possible.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And within four or six weeks, I finally got my number and could emigrate to England.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think either 16 or 17.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, how Mrs.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Landmann heard about us, I do not know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "After she told us, she made the arrangements, apparently, with an organization at the British embassy in Berlin that handled these Kindertransports.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had to fill out or my mother had to fill out certain questionnaires about me and about my religion, when I was born, where I was born, and that she would be willing to release me, even if she would never see me again.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as I said, all of this helped a great deal.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I did not have a passport.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, no Jews had passports, except what they call [GERMAN] or stateless passports.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I could not have emigrated anymore to any other country in 1939.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the Kindertransports did not need a passport.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Do you recall how long these arrangements took?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as I said, we heard from Mrs.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Landmann the first time either in December of '38 or January of '39.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And by February the 8th, I was already out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it could only have taken six weeks or eight weeks at the very most.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, he was very much in agreement because he realized that Hitler will be there for good, that you simply couldn't overthrow him by that time.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had annexed Austria and was more powerful than ever.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
